<dl id="n30173g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30173g">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30173g"> 173(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pavor nocturnus</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Allied to nightmare are the night-terrors of children. <mark><i>Pavor nocturnus</i></mark>, as it is called in medicine, is a vivid and highly disagreeable dream produced usually by some abnormal state of an internal organ, often colic. <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 63</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
